items.name: Buffalo Chicken Meatballs
items.description: Spicy, flavorful and—best of all—easy to make. Buffalo chicken meatballs will be a hit at any party.

items.name: Mini Corn Muffins with Spicy Cheddar Filling
items.description: I’m an Iowa gardener and I like to feature sweet corn in my recipes. These cute, easy-to-eat bites are a fun change from the usual appetizers. —Margaret Blair, Lorimor, Iowa

items.name: Homemade Guacamole
items.description: I always judge a Tex-Mex restaurant by its guacamole. And although it's simple to prepare, it can go wrong oh, so easily. I've spent many years perfecting mine, to the point where I think it's better than most restaurants.

items.name: Cream Cheese Ham Roll-Ups
items.description: Green onions and ripe olives give lively flavor to these bite-size appetizers from Kathleen Green of Republic, Missouri. “They’re quick to assemble and can be made the day before they’re needed,” she notes. “They’re very popular with my friends and family.”

items.name: JERK CHICKEN
items.description: The spice is the bringer of flavour to this party.

items.name: SHEPHERD’S PIE
items.description: A British classic! Done properly, this is a dish to be proud of.

items.name: WHOLE SATAY CHICKEN
items.description: A little spicy, nutty and naughty! Cooked slowly, so you’ll need to be patient.

items.name: COTTAGE PIE WITH BLUE CHEESE MASH
items.description: The classic comfort food, this one with added blue cheese and a dash of curry powder.

items.name: ​​Spanish-Style Pasta Salad with Tuna and Marinated Tomatoes
items.description: Spanish pantry staples like mildly spicy and sweet piparra peppers and tangy sherry vinegar bring bold flavor to this hearty pasta salad from 2015 F&W Best New Chef Katie Button.

items.name: Cucumber Salad
items.description: Vinegar, sugar, salt, and onion add gentle, versatile flavor to this quick and easy cucumber salad recipe. Feel free to make this a day ahead and store it in the fridge

items.name: Vegetable Rainbow Salad
items.description: This vibrant salad showcases a colorful mixture of pickled onions and radishes, roasted root vegetables, leafy greens, and black quinoa.

items.name: Cobb Salad with Roasted Sweet Onion Dressing
items.description: Everything you love about a Cobb salad is taken to the next level with a roasted garlic and onion vinaigrette

items.name: White Bean Soup with Bacon and Herbs
items.description: The Spanish dish caldo gallego is the inspiration for this warming soup, combining the heartiness of white beans and crisp bacon with a light, herb-infused broth. To keep things vegetarian, you can swap the bacon fat for olive oil or butter and top the soup with another crunchy garnish of your liking, such as croutons.

items.name: Classic Split Pea Soup
items.description: I haven't met a bean or pea that I didn't love, says chef Steven Satterfield. Here, he soaks split peas for an hour before simmering them in the soup, so they're more tender and the soup is smoother.

items.name: Classic Chicken Noodle Soup
items.description: The queen of comforting soups, this deeply flavorful chicken noodle soup recipe is a tried-and-true classic.

items.name: Lentil and Garlic-Sausage Soup
items.description: A riff on a classic Italian dish, this garlicky lentil soup skews pan-European, with French lentils, Manchego cheese, and any really good garlic sausage.

items.name: Triple Chocolate Cookies
items.description: These triple chocolate cookies are made with cocoa powder, chocolate chips, and chocolate chunks! These are the ultimate cookies for real chocolate lovers.

items.name: Puff Pastry Apple Tart
items.description: This puff pastry apple tart is the perfect easy apple dessert. It is made with caramelized apples and store-bought puff pastry!

items.name: Cherry Galette
items.description: This decadent and easy cherry galette is made with a buttery flakey crust and filled with a delicious cherry filling.

items.name: Strawberry Shortcake Cake
items.description: This strawberry shortcake birthday cake is made with a tender vanilla cake, filled with whipped cream and fresh juicy strawberries.

items.name: Key Lime Martini
items.description: Have your favorite dessert in cocktail form! Tropical flavors like key lime juice, cream of coconut and pineapple juice blend together for a tart, sweet and creamy beverage.

items.name: Watermelon-Strawberry Cooler
items.description: My family gulps this frosty cooler because we love, love, love watermelon. The strawberries give it an extra pop. This is a perfect drink for Texas heat.

items.name: Banana Daiquiri
items.description: When life gives you ripe bananas, try this tiki treat at home! Pull out the blender and whirl together a glass of this slushy rum-lime-and-banana bliss. —Taste of Home Test Kitchen

items.name: Peach Sangria Recipe
items.description: White wine lovers will swoon for this crisp and gorgeous sangria. The star of the show is the sliced fruit, followed by a potent

items.name: Sweet ‘n’ Tangy Chicken Wings
items.description: I love the convenience of slow-cooker recipes for get-togethers. Start these sweet and sour chicken wings a few hours ahead of time and you'll have fantastic appetizers ready when your guests arrive. —Ida Tuey, South Lyon, Michigan

items.name: Brownie Batter Dip
items.description: Our brownie batter dip gives you all the flavor and none of the bake time of true brownies. It's perfect for when you're craving brownies but don't want to turn on the oven.

items.name: Shrimp Cocktail
items.description: During the ’60s, shrimp cocktail was one of the most popular party foods around. And it is still a crowd favorite. It’s the one appetizer that I serve for every special occasion as well as for munchie meals. —Peggy Allen, Pasadena, California

items.name: Celebration Cheese Balls
items.description: A handful of simple ingredients that go together in minutes, three fun flavorful options…these creamy cheese balls from our Test Kitchen are a

items.name: CLASSIC CHICKEN KYIV
items.description: Who doesn’t love chicken Kiev? I think it’s the best thing ever!

items.name: JERK CHICKEN AND TOMATO SALAD
items.description: The punchy coating and seasoning with a fiery Caribbean heat.

items.name: SLOW ROASTED LAMB WITH HOT FENNEL RELISH
items.description: Slow roasting lamb allows all of those lovely flavours and juices to render and mix together.

items.name: LAMB TAGINE WITH CHICKPEAS
items.description: Lamb stands up well to strong flavours like the harissa and dried mint in this aromatic tagine.

items.name: Peppery Greens Salad with Avocado, Chicken, and Tortilla Croutons
items.description: Justin Chapple tosses arugula, frisée, chicken, radicchio, avocado, pepitas, and tortilla pieces with a simple peppery dressing for this visually appealing salad.

items.name: Charred Cabbage Salad with Pecan Dukkah and Chile-Lime Butter
items.description: Nick Cobarruvias seasons charred cabbage with chile-lime butter, which is mildly spicy from árbol chiles and bright from lime zest

items.name: Tomato, Basil, and Cucumber Panzanella with Grated Tomato Balsamic Vinaigrette
items.description: Pair oven-roasted sourdough croutons with juicy ripe tomatoes, raw red onion, and crisp cucumbers in this summer salad from Samin Nosrat,

items.name: Black Rice Salad with Cherries and Plums
items.description: Fresh plums and cherries add pops of juicy sweetness to this hearty summer salad.

items.name: Bún Bò Huế (Vietnamese Vermicelli Noodle Soup with Sliced Beef)
items.description: Topped with a multitude of garnishes, this aromatic and savory soup from Mailynh Phan features lemongrass-infused bone broth with vermicelli noodles and tender beef.

items.name: Leftover Roast Turkey and Chinese Egg Noodle Soup
items.description: Andrea Nguyen was inspired by Vietnam's roast duck–egg noodle soup, called mi vit tiem, to make this mi ga tay ('mee ga tey'),

items.name: Butternut Squash Soup with Bacon and Crème Fraîche
items.description: Roasting the butternut squash with honey and a touch of salt intensifies its natural sweetness, and browning the onions low and slow deepens the foundational flavor of this hearty soup.

items.name: Chunky Tomato Soup
items.description: For the best texture in this vibrant tomato soup, puree half of the soup until smooth, then stir it into the chunky base.

items.name: Lemon Tiramisu
items.description: This fresh lemon tiramisu is made with lemon curd, lemon mascarpone cream, and with ladyfingers dipped in limoncello.

items.name: Mini Fruit Tarts
items.description: These mini fruit tarts are made with easy and buttery tart shells, filled with homemade pastry cream, and topped with fresh fruit

items.name: Strawberry Cheesecake Cookies
items.description: These strawberry cheesecake cookies are soft and sweet, loaded with fresh strawberries, and filled with creamy cheesecake filling.

items.name: Tiramisu Cake With Mascarpone Cream
items.description: This tiramisu cake is made with genoise cake soaked with espresso filled with mascarpone cream, and topped with cocoa powder.

items.name: Raspberry Iced Tea
items.description: One sip and you'll likely agree that this is the best flavored tea you've ever tasted. —Chris Wilson, Sellersville, Pennsylvania

items.name: Cherry Fruit Smoothies
items.description: You need just four ingredients to blend together these super-fast smoothies for breakfast. Try whipping them up on a hot summer day for a cool and refreshing treat. —Macy Plummer, Avon, Indiana

items.name: Iced Melon Moroccan Mint Tea
items.description: I grow mint on my balcony, and this refreshing beverage is a wonderful way to use it. It combines two of my favorite drinks—Moroccan Mint Tea and Honeydew Agua Fresca.

items.name: Rhubarb Mint Tea
items.description: A bumper crop of rhubarb and mint from my garden inspired me to create this thirst-quenching pick-me-up. Raspberries deepen the tea's vibrant red color, making the drinks a pretty addition to your table. —Laurie Bock, Lynden, Washington
